<br>
Monks offer pulling and cr expertise to groups as well as decent damage and can work as a tank in a pinch even though they instituted the ac cap. <br>
<br>
Wizards have ports can ghetto mez with root, snare to prevent runner, and also has low resist and big boom nukes with various different resist checks. Also can solo quad quite well in the planes.<br>
<br>
Magician have Pets DSand Nukes everything else can easily be taken care of by that Mages who has been lfg at zone in for 3 hours if you really think about it.Trods have become more of a convenience item and all our summons are permanent for the most part. <br>
<br>
The bolt isnt the incredible nuke that wizards are claiming it is. The bolt has severe limitations. No matter how many wizards claim that magicians hit the bolt np in groups, thats an out and out falicy. I cant tell you how many times ive had the bolt miss the target for seemingly no reason or get blocked by someone who moved into my los at the last second. Also if the mob is fire resistant we have to go down to SoS a 825 pt nuke if that will even land. Wizards dont have this problem because they have nukes for all occasions. Wizards arent all about damage they are all about the variety of ways they can do damage they can do nuke damage no matter the mobs resists.<br>
