<br>
Since the game began spells have been easier to come by than weapons. Weapons and armour you went out and adventured for, spells for the most part were available from vendors or through research of varying difficulty.<br>
<br>
In RoK spells become a bit harder to get, with some being rather rare drops. However a mage was still able to get by with his pets, they were available en masse, a few were quite rare but at level 60 you were rewarded with the easier to get version of the water pet.<br>
<br>
In Velious a mage could expect to get all of their spells through the course of normal adventuring. The hardest to get spells dropped from dragons in Western Wastes that are doable with single groups. Other spells were more common.<br>
<br>
In SoL many spells dropped from named mobs of varying dificulty, and quickly became available to the average joe mage for a few thousand plat. Prices were more expensive if you wanted them <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>now</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> but trickle was very, very fast.<br>
<br>
Why should the basic underlying principle of the game that spells are in general easier to come by than weapons change because these spells happen to be quite good?<br>
<br>
I'm sorry Cyricus, you are a good guy, but if you think I should walk around with my <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>pets</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, the very core of my class, being gimped just because I don't play the raiding game you know where you can shove that idea.<br>
