</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=h0gfather>H0gfather</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 691<br> <font color=#333333>(11/8/02 2:06:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=394.topic&index=118>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.aus-1.au.nu/images/photo.gif width=90 height=112></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: It Begins</span><hr size=1> You may not be here to make friends Cyricus, but like it or not you are as a moderator here to represent the best interests of all Magicians in the Tower, and more broadly every Magician in the game, given that this is the epicentre of a much broader player base.<br>
<br>
I cannot in all conscience understand how you could wish for your fellow Mages to be nerfed. The only conclusion I can draw is that in your Ivory Tower you consider the rest of us unworthy of these new pets and spells.<br>
<br>
You have been a good friend of mine for a long time now, and I have enjoyed the discussions we have had. Please, don't message me in game anymore, I don't want to hear from you. Your superior, pious attitude makes me sick to bne honest, how dare you dictate to the entire body of Mages that we should not be able to finally, after all this waiting - two years in the making - receive new upgraded pets and a genuine nuke upgrade.<br>
<br>
We've been playing the same game as you, we've done it just as hard as you. Just because you are in an upper tier raiding guild means you get to say what we do and do not deserve in a new expansion?<br>
<br>
I am honestly stunned that you could so brazenly come out and say such a thing. You strike down your own class mates! I know The Companions made out like bandits on the Tribunal from spell drop sales in Luclin, I paid over 40k to you guys for mine, and the current rumour is that you guys gleaned well over one million platinum pieces in spell sales alone. Is this the problem? Mandoman not able to line the guild coffers this time because <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>we can actually go out and get our own damn spells without having to pay you guys</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->?<br>
<br>
Damn you to hell. Personal attack yes, but damn you Cyricus. You can use your admin powers and ban me form the board if you want, I could care less. If this is what the moderators have come to here, if this is what the Tower stands for, keeping the average joe mage down, then I want nothing of it. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=h0gfather>H0gfather</A> at: 11/8/02 2:11:18 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vhailordarsithanon@themagicianstower>Vhailor Darsithanon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#333333>(11/8/02 2:29:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=394.topic&index=119>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: It Begins</span><hr size=1>      I am so SICK of the snobbish attitudes that come to the forefront in this game. In my time here at the tower I have had the likes of Noonie tell me I have no right to bitch about the DPS and mitigation abilities of the GV pets. In a nutshell I was told by Noonie &quot;I used to feel the way you do when I was your level...but now I don't...get over it.&quot; Followed by,&quot;Maybe you should try parsing the damage sometime before you leap to these judgements.&quot; I have and do parse...I simply had my opinions disregarded and belittled because I was not &quot;Important&quot; enough to have a valid concern and thusly it was assumed that I was too stupid to have done research or have amassed any data. What prompted this? A &quot;It was ok for me to bitch when I was your level but now I am level 60 and MY pets got upgraded so bugger off.&quot; attitude.<br>
<br>
     I have been told on the serverwide channel that I would be laughed out of PoP if I tried to get a group there with my current gear by Myrradin. (sp?) Granted it was my fault for asking if I could survive grouped there in my gimptastic gear...but still would a bit of compassion for &quot;Joe Average&quot; be too much to ask. Perhaps some positive reinforcement or advice instead of mockery and laughter?<br>
<br>
     Now a new attitude rears its ugly head...61 plus spells should only be available from raid mobs??? Cyricus let me ask you...if all that raid loot doesn't clearly enough separate you (a raider) from me (a gimp) then why do better equipped people spend so much time laughing at and mocking people with a similar gear loadout to mine? Why are people in my gear/guild situation relegated to watching from the sidelines as noncontributers?<br>
<br>
     The only conclusion that I can draw is that obviously its not enough to have one piece of gear that nets the stats of any four pieces of gear possessed by &quot;Joe Average&quot;. Obviously all those right clickies some of us will never see are not enough. I suppose the only way some people will be happy is if &quot;Joe Average&quot; doesn't sully the Planes with our presence unless we are willing to ass kiss our way into Uber Guild_001....at least until the &quot;Upper Crust&quot; is far enough into the planes that we will not get in the way. Oh yeah and until the &quot;Upper Crust&quot; has managed to farm enough droppable loot and spells to rape and pillage &quot;Joe Average&quot; out of cash he doesn't have...all the while laughing at how gimp the stuff they are charging 100k for is compared to the gear they are wearing.<br>
<br>
     I will not deny the accomplishments of the above Mages nor will I dispute their contributions to our class as a whole...especially not Cyricus who for a long time I have believed to be our number one contributor. That being said...the above attitude not just in the framework of a single class but in the framework of the game as a whole, is utter and complete garbage.<br>
<br>
     Anyone who feels that only the upper 10% of the population of a game with a patronage of over 400,000 should be allowed to progress and have fun needs the jaws of life to pull their head out of their ass.<br>
<br>
Vhailor Darsithanon<br>
Bertoxx<br>
<br>
P.S. And before any flames start shooting in...no I am not a disgruntled ex or wannabe Uberguilder. I am precisely where I want to be and doing what I want to do. I do not &quot;Hate on&quot; Uberguilders as a rule and I could care less about all the &quot;Mine is bigger&quot; piece waving. When I do get pissed is when it is being insinuated that people like me do not deserve to play this game,enjoy this game or advance in this game because some of the &quot;Upper Crust&quot; do not believe we have &quot;Earned&quot; it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=calebe>Calebe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 542<br> <font color=#333333>(11/8/02 2:32:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=394.topic&index=120>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: It Begins</span><hr size=1> Strong words Hogfeather, but I agree it sounds like Cyruis wants not only better equipement, better effects, better pets (hello gloves of dark summoning), but wants to ensure that no magician but people that raid in the top guilds should ever get anything without them SELLING it to you.<br>
